{"TopicId":148665,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Terminology: Kerbin system apses","CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T02:15:53Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T02:15:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP is rocket science, serious stuff, precise engineering... To match this level of technology, everything must be perfect, and very specific. And we are just sitting here saying apoasis and periapsis in all situations. Enough! Time has come to solve this \u003Cem\u003Ecritical \u003C/em\u003Eproblem and find new terms for the apses of the Kerbin system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have come up with a few, feel free to suggest your own, so that together we can \u003Cs\u003Emake Kerbin great again\u003C/s\u003E finally say the right things when needed!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EMoho\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerimoeorivicikion, Apomoeorivicikion (from Mohorovi\u010Di\u0107, \u0022h\u0022 replaced by \u0022e\u0022 since eta is historically called heta,\u00A0\u0022k\u0022 added to make it sound greeker, excessive length and unpronounceability\u00A0is intended)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerimoe, Apimoe\u003Cbr\u003E\n[periapsis term not specified],\u00A0\u00A0Ramadamadamadingdong (by Aperture Science)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EEve\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerievon, Apoevon (pretty obvious)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerieev, Apoeev\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EGilly\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerigille, Apogille (Gilly doesn\u0027t sound Greek at all so no \u0022on\u0022 but an \u0022e\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EKerbin\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerikeron, Apokeron (because whatever you say, \u0022perikerb\u0022 or \u0022perikerbon\u0022 just sounds bad)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerikee, Apokee (-gee with a \u0022k\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EMun\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerimynthion, Apomynthion (-cynthion with an \u0022m\u0022 because we say \u0022munar\u0022)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerimune, Apomune (-lune with an \u0022m\u0022)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeriloon, Apiloon\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EMinmus\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeriminimuse, Apominimuse (Minmus sounds like a contraction of minimus, so \u0022i\u0022 added; kept the \u0022e\u0022 of perimune)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerimuse, Apomuse (derived from perimune, with an \u0022s\u0022)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerimint, Apimint (by 5thHorseman)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EDuna\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeridunon, Apodunon (pretty obvious)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeridoon, Apidoon\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EIke\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerikon, Apoikon (pretty obvious)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EDres\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPericemeterion, Apocemeterion (Dres is supposed to be Ceres, Ceres is a Roman goddess called Demeter in Greek; so if\u00A0Ceres = Demeter, then\u00A0Deres = Cemeter)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeridree, Apidree\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EJool\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerijole, Apojole (derived from -jove, jovian...)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerizoone, Apozoone (from perizene, with more oo)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerijule, Apijule\u003Cbr\u003E\nApojoo, Perijoo (by Van Disaster)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003ELaythe\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerilythion, Apolythion (dropped the \u0022a\u0022 because I think it sounds more natural this way)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerilaythion, Apolaythion (sounds natural enough if you pronounce \u0022ay\u0022 as one sound, not two)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EVall\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerivallon, Apovallon (pretty obvious)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeriveikon, Apoveikon (from the Greek word for \u0022wall\u0022:\u00A0\u0022teikos\u0022 with a \u0022v\u0022 instead of a \u0022t\u0022 to make it closer to Vall)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003ETylo\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerityle, Apotyle (pretty obvious)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EBop\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeribopion, Apobopion (pretty obvious)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EPol\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPeripalion, Apopalion (Greek root of \u0022pollen\u0022 is \u0022pale\u0022)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerigyron, Apogyron (Google Translate says the Greek for \u0022pollen\u0022 is \u0022gyri\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003EEeloo\u003C/u\u003E:\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerikelyon, Apokelyon (from \u0022cheli\u0022 the Greek for \u0022eel\u0022, with a \u0022y\u0022 added since upsilon is the equivalent of the \u0022oo\u0022 sound)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerilyon, Apoilyon (\u0022ee\u0022 replaced with an \u0022i\u0022 and \u0022oo\u0022 with \u0022y\u0022)\u003Cbr\u003E\nPerieel, Apoeel\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-27T16:22:26Z\u0022 title=\u002209/27/2016 04:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gaarst\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Martian Emigrant","CreatedById":158362,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T02:28:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell. I\u0027ll be.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat should straighten any crooked mal-sayer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll start practising right away.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerimune, Apomune (-lune with an \u0022m\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI though that Perimune was a WW2 German military base...Shows what I know.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nME\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpacedCowboy","CreatedById":92106,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T02:29:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s all \u0022Greek to me!\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T03:57:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u0027Perikee, Apokee (-gee with a \u0022k\u0022)\u003C/em\u003E\u0027 - please don\u0027t do that, this randomly replacing first letter with K thing always has been awful. \u0022-keron\u0022 leads to Kerosyncronous, which is pleasant, I like that lots. I guess Apoke and Perike ( spoken A-po-K and Per-i-K ) aren\u0027t terrible too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot a fan of contracting Laythe at all though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T04:40:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow about a generic term instead of a lot of specific terms? \u0022My probe is approaching perithingamajig!\u0022\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pincushionman","CreatedById":98495,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T04:57:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo we really have such terms in real life for All the moons? I was under the impression that we only really used -helion, -gee, and -cynthion very much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(and I swear\u00A0I saw -selene used\u00A0rather than -cynthion once. Might have been when reading Lost Moon)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-26T04:59:45Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2016 04:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by pincushionman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"stibbons","CreatedById":57865,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T05:19:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI strictly use \u0022near end\u0022 and \u0022far end\u0022 to describe my orbits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T07:59:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny, we were having the same discussion in another thread. Here\u0027s the work-in-progress list we\u0027ve come up with so far:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApimoe/Perimoe\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApoeev/Perieev\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApokee/Perikee\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApiloon/Periloon\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApimint/Perimint\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApidoon/Peridoon\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApidree/Peridree\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApijule/Perijule\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApoeel/Perieel\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ElWanderer","CreatedById":114015,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T08:01:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774514\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474865850\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298495\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pincushionman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, pincushionman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo we really have such terms in real life for All the moons? I was under the impression that we only really used -helion, -gee, and -cynthion very much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(and I swear\u00A0I saw -selene used\u00A0rather than -cynthion once. Might have been when reading Lost Moon)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerilune and periselene are also used for the Moon, yeah.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve heard perijove (Jupiter) quite a few times recently. Guess the rarer ones only get brought out whenever there is a probe arriving at a body! Wikipedia has a list, though it doesn\u0027t have any for moons of bodies other than Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T11:30:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhilst \u0027body specific\u0027 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E terms can certainly have their uses, I think that for in game use and general confusion avoidance we need to stick to the current generic terms.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, there could be a real danger of scaring off newcomers to the game and forums with unnecessary technical terms if we\u0027re not careful. \u00A0This game can be hard enough to learn anyway, without what can come across as \u0027Veteran players\u0027 talking down to \u0027Noobs\u0027. \u00A0If the new players have spent time on less welcoming games and forums then that may well be what they have experienced and therefore the impression they get, I know that we are better than that, but newcomers might not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T11:44:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474862227\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Van Disaster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Van Disaster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u0027Perikee, Apokee (-gee with a \u0022k\u0022)\u003C/em\u003E\u0027 - please don\u0027t do that, this randomly replacing first letter with K thing always has been awful. \u0022-keron\u0022 leads to Kerosyncronous, which is pleasant, I like that lots. I guess Apoke and Perike ( spoken A-po-K and Per-i-K ) aren\u0027t terrible too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot a fan of contracting Laythe at all though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t like the adding \u0022k\u0022 thing either, but I\u0027ve seen perikee/apokee used a few times so I figured out I might as well have put it. (Note that all other \u0022k\u0022 I\u0027ve added in these words are because of a (fictive or not)\u00A0Greek root, not to make them \u0022more kerbal\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Laythe it really depends on how you pronounce it, I tend to say it la-ee-the (the \u0022ay\u0022 being two syllabes) but saying Lay-the (\u0022ay\u0022 one sound) also works and does make perilaythion more pleasant; I\u0027ll add it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774514\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474865850\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298495\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pincushionman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, pincushionman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo we really have such terms in real life for All the moons? I was under the impression that we only really used -helion, -gee, and -cynthion very much.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(and I swear\u00A0I saw -selene used\u00A0rather than -cynthion once. Might have been when reading Lost Moon)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSun: perihelion/apohelion\u003Cbr\u003E\nMercury: perihermion/apohermion\u003Cbr\u003E\nVenus: pericytherion/apocytherion\u003Cbr\u003E\nEarth: perigee/apogee\u003Cbr\u003E\nMoon: perilune/apolune, periselene/aposelene, pericynthion/apocynthion\u003Cbr\u003E\nMars: periareion/apoareion\u003Cbr\u003E\nJupiter: perjove/apojove, perizene/apozene\u003Cbr\u003E\nSaturn: perikrone/apokrone\u003Cbr\u003E\nUranus: periuranion/apouranion\u003Cbr\u003E\nNeptune: periposeidon/apoposeidon\u003Cbr\u003E\nPluto: perihadeion/apohadeion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474876769\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brikoleur\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Brikoleur said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny, we were having the same discussion in another thread. Here\u0027s the work-in-progress list we\u0027ve come up with so far:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApimoe/Perimoe\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApoeev/Perieev\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApokee/Perikee\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApiloon/Periloon\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApimint/Perimint\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApidoon/Peridoon\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApidree/Peridree\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApijule/Perijule\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EApoeel/Perieel\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook a few posts up in your thread,\u00A0I was the one suggesting names for apses in KSP right before making this thread \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdding these.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774803\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474889441\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022130621\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pandaman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, pandaman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhilst \u0027body specific\u0027 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E terms can certainly have their uses, I think that for in game use and general confusion avoidance we need to stick to the current generic terms.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, there could be a real danger of scaring off newcomers to the game and forums with unnecessary technical terms if we\u0027re not careful. \u00A0This game can be hard enough to learn anyway, without what can come across as \u0027Veteran players\u0027 talking down to \u0027Noobs\u0027. \u00A0If the new players have spent time on less welcoming games and forums then that may well be what they have experienced and therefore the impression they get, I know that we are better than that, but newcomers might not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is more a joke than anything really, I\u0027m not suggesting the game should replace \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E by things as absurd as perimoeorivicikion or perigyron. I would make the effort to learn them all if it did\u00A0though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-26T11:49:45Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2016 11:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gaarst\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T11:46:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought this was intended more as whimsy than a serious attempt at changing the terminology.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpeaking as a relative newcomer to KSP \u2013 although I don\u0027t consider myself a newbie, not since I managed to put a 140-ton \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E spaceplane into orbit using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E \u2013 there is a fair bit of Kerbal idiom here already, and I for one have found it charming rather than intimidating, and I\u0027m greatly enjoying the process of learning it. I\u0027ve also\u00A0developed a healthy skepticism of any words with a \u0022K\u0022 in them, ever since I thought Kolniya was a real orbit...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T12:57:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774813\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474890290\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t like the adding \u0022k\u0022 thing either, but I\u0027ve seen perikee/apokee used a few times so I figured out I might as well have put it. (Note that all other \u0022k\u0022 I\u0027ve added in these words are because of a (fictive or not)\u00A0Greek root, not to make them \u0022more kerbal\u0022)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor Laythe it really depends on how you pronounce it, I tend to say it la-ee-the (the \u0022ay\u0022 being two syllabes) but saying Lay-the (\u0022ay\u0022 one sound) also works and does make perilaythion more pleasant; I\u0027ll add it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSun: perihelion/apohelion\u003Cbr\u003E\nMercury: perihermion/apohermion\u003Cbr\u003E\nVenus: pericytherion/apocytherion\u003Cbr\u003E\nEarth: perigee/apogee\u003Cbr\u003E\nMoon: perilune/apolune, periselene/aposelene, pericynthion/apocynthion\u003Cbr\u003E\nMars: periareion/apoareion\u003Cbr\u003E\nJupiter: perjove/apojove, perizene/apozene\u003Cbr\u003E\nSaturn: perikrone/apokrone\u003Cbr\u003E\nUranus: periuranion/apouranion\u003Cbr\u003E\nNeptune: periposeidon/apoposeidon\u003Cbr\u003E\nPluto: perihadeion/apohadeion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLook a few posts up in your thread,\u00A0I was the one suggesting names for apses in KSP right before making this thread \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdding these.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is more a joke than anything really, I\u0027m not suggesting the game should replace \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Apoapsis\u0022\u003EAp\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E by things as absurd as perimoeorivicikion or perigyron. I would make the effort to learn them all if it did\u00A0though \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T13:12:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKIC 8462852 = Perikic8462852ion = [perikeiaieseitmiljenfohandredthauzandsixtitueithandredfiftituon]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(beware mistakes, not a native speaker)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: Also not sure about emphasis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-26T13:16:48Z\u0022 title=\u002209/26/2016 01:16  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T19:56:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474856153\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP is rocket science, serious stuff, precise engineering...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m unable to reply since every time I get this far in the text my parser breaks down with \u0027does not compute\u0027 and refuses to redo from start.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T20:54:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474856153\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerimo\u003Cs\u003Eeorivicikion\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo many weird letters. I\u0027ll settle for \u0022Perimo\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T22:27:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suggest changing the Moho apogee to \u0022ramadamadamadingdong\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-26T22:48:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore I played KSP, in my stories when needing to talk about orbits around stars other than the Sun I used \u0022periastron\u0022 and \u0022apastron.\u0022 I don\u0027t know where I got them or if I made them up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWere I to write them today I\u0027d probably use -apsis. And I\u0027d probably not even notice I was doing so \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Oh and I take credit for perimint and apomint for Minmus)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Martian Emigrant","CreatedById":158362,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T00:25:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222775453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474923283\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo many weird letters. I\u0027ll settle for \u0022Perimo\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWasn\u0027t that a signer?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nME\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Van Disaster","CreatedById":58876,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T03:26:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re not being serious Apojoo \u0026amp; Perijoo for Jool are far too fun to leave off \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E Apoloo?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T15:35:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474864811\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9/26/2016 at 5:40 AM, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow about a generic term instead of a lot of specific terms? \u0022My probe is approaching perithingamajig!\u0022\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u0027appy with a perry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T16:22:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222774881\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474895576\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 26/09/2016 at 2:12 PM, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKIC 8462852 = Perikic8462852ion = [perikeiaieseitmiljenfohandredthauzandsixtitueithandredfiftituon]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(beware mistakes, not a native speaker)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: Also not sure about emphasis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBu KIC 8462852 is not part of the Kerbal system, I can\u0027t add it to the list, I agree with the term though it\u0027s precise and everyone can understand it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222775367\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474919815\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m unable to reply since every time I get this far in the text my parser breaks down with \u0027does not compute\u0027 and refuses to redo from start.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPsssh, it\u0027s because you can\u0027t see the beauty of a well-engineered \u003Cs\u003Eexplosion\u003C/s\u003E rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222775453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474923283\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cubinator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, cubinator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo many weird letters. I\u0027ll settle for \u0022Perimo\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerimo for short, but I\u0027m keeping\u00A0perimoeorivicikion. Also we already have perimoe/apomoe\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222775598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474928840\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152223\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aperture Science\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Aperture Science said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suggest changing the Moho apogee to \u0022ramadamadamadingdong\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdded it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222775628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474930127\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore I played KSP, in my stories when needing to talk about orbits around stars other than the Sun I used \u0022periastron\u0022 and \u0022apastron.\u0022 I don\u0027t know where I got them or if I made them up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWere I to write them today I\u0027d probably use -apsis. And I\u0027d probably not even notice I was doing so \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Oh and I take credit for perimint and apomint for Minmus)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeriastron and apastron are usually used when describing orbits around stars other than the Sun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdded your mention next to perimint and apomint.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222775914\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474946808\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Van Disaster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Van Disaster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027re not being serious Apojoo \u0026amp; Perijoo for Jool are far too fun to leave off \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E Apoloo?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdding it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T16:26:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222776521\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474993348\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPsssh, it\u0027s because you can\u0027t see the beauty of a well-engineered \u003Cs\u003Eexplosion\u003C/s\u003E rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tracked down my parser crashes to the concept of \u0022KSP\u0022 and \u0022serious\u0022 in the same sentence.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll continue to debug my parser.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T16:27:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222776530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474993591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107529\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Curveball Anders\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Curveball Anders said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tracked down my parser crashes to the concept of \u0022KSP\u0022 and \u0022serious\u0022 in the same sentence.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll continue to debug my parser.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat, did you think KSP was a game?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-27T16:27:24Z\u0022 title=\u002209/27/2016 04:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Gaarst\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-27T16:30:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222776531\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022148665\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474993638\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126740\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gaarst\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Gaarst said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat, did you think KSP was a game?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course not, it\u0027s a simulation of life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust not a very serious simulation of life, rather a simulation of a not very serious life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}